criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          1. aged between 18 ~ 65 years old;

          2. at least 4 weeks since onset of onset of wound;

          3. healing wound with at least 6 scores in Modified Vancouver Scar Scale for more than
             four weeks

          4. the most important of all, read and signed the inform concern of this study.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          1. patients with open wound;

          2. oxygen dependent

          3. having evidence of cognitive deficit;

          4. having local infection, severe inflammation or otherwise lesion that is not suggestive
             for ESWT;

          5. patient with serious medical problems, as uncontrolled hypertension, coagulopathy,
             recent severe hemorrhage, neoplasm, severe hepatic disease, epilepsy, cutaneous
             pathology, mental retardation.
